{"type":"message","id":"531c0bd5","parentId":"3824cb70","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:20:09.215Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lwp72ozc7ehs_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 051923\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: TIC (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) which is the next action item. The goal is to:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLet me look at what pulse logs exist and what the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY document says about the approach.\r\n\r\nI should start by implementing a basic TIC classifier that:\r\n- Reads recent pulse logs\r\n- Identifies invariant patterns (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n- Identifies variant patterns (things that change between pulses)\r\n- Attempts to predict the next pulse based on invariants\r\n\r\nLet me write a Python script that does this analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier that identifies invariant vs. variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy. I need to build the initial implementation to measure baseline performance.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate Python script implementing Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier that analyzes pulse logs, identifies patterns, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_metadata(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key metadata from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    metadata = {\r\n        'path': filepath,\r\n        'timestamp': None,\r\n        'has_mutation': False,\r\n        'observation': '',\r\n        'action': '',\r\n        'files_touched': [],\r\n        'word_count': len(content.split())\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract observation/action if present\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r'### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    act_match = re.search(r'### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    if obs_match:\r\n        metadata['observation'] = obs_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    if act_match:\r\n        metadata['action'] = act_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    # Check for mutations\r\n    if 'No mutations applied' not in content:\r\n        mutation_match = re.search(r'### MUTATION\\s*\\n```\\n(.+?)```', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n        if mutation_match:\r\n            metadata['has_mutation'] = True\r\n            # Extract file paths from mutation\r\n            file_matches = re.findall(r'file:\\s*([^\\s]+)', mutation_match.group(1))\r\n            metadata['files_touched'] = file_matches\r\n    \r\n    # Extract timestamp from filename\r\n    ts_match = PULSE_PATTERN.match(filepath.name)\r\n    if ts_match:\r\n        ts_str = ts_match.group(1)\r\n        metadata['timestamp'] = datetime.strptime(ts_str, \"%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S\")\r\n    \r\n    return metadata\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngrams(text, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as potential invariant patterns.\"\"\"\r\n    words = text.lower().split()\r\n    ngrams = []\r\n    for i in range(len(words) - n + 1):\r\n        ngram = ' '.join(words[i:i+n])\r\n        ngrams.append(ngram)\r\n    return set(ngrams)\r\n\r\ndef identify_invariants(pulses, top_k=50):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Identify patterns that appear consistently across pulses.\r\n    These represent 'causal structure' - invariant relationships.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    # Count pattern frequencies\r\n    pattern_counts = defaultdict(int)\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        text = f\"{pulse['observation']} {pulse['action']}\"\r\n        ngrams = compute_ngrams(text)\r\n        for ngram in ngrams:\r\n            pattern_counts[ngram] += 1\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants = patterns appearing in >50% of pulses\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {p for p, count in pattern_counts.items() if count >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    # Return top-k by frequency\r\n    sorted_invariants = sorted(pattern_counts.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])\r\n    return sorted_invariants[:top_k]\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    text = f\"{pulse['observation']} {pulse['action']}\"\r\n    ngrams = compute_ngrams(text)\r\n    \r\n    invariant_count = len(ngrams & set(invariants))\r\n    total_count = len(ngrams)\r\n    \r\n    if total_count == 0:\r\n        return {'invariant_ratio': 0, 'variant_ratio': 1, 'classification': 'variant'}\r\n    \r\n    ratio = invariant_count / total_count\r\n    # >40% invariant content = invariant classification\r\n    classification = 'invariant' if ratio >= 0.4 else 'variant'\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'invariant_ratio': ratio,\r\n        'variant_ratio': 1 - ratio,\r\n        'classification': classification\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(prior_pulses, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Predict characteristics of next pulse based on invariants.\r\n    Returns: dict\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:19:55\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774344009214}}
{"type":"message","id":"2f687935","parentId":"531c0bd5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:20:19.382Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"b41c203c727827046abd16563ebde9199a41e9b56109e22945d73a30ef6d00b2"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 05:19 AM\n\n**Status:** ✅ Complete (3 pulse logs processed, 1 mutation proposed)\n\n**What happened:**\n- Previous cycle detected a major insight: **Compression and Causal Discovery are the same problem**\n- The next logical step was identified: **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment**\n- A Python script was drafted to implement the TIC classifier — designed to identify invariant vs. variant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\n\n**Proposed Mutation:**\n- A new `tic_classifier.py` script was outlined (partial) that would:\n  - Extract n-gram patterns from pulse observations/actions\n  - Identify invariants (patterns in >50% of pulses → causal structure)\n  - Classify pulse content as invariant or variant\n  - Attempt to predict next pulse characteristics\n\n**Active Questions for Next Cycle:**\n- The mutation script was only partially generated (code was cut off mid-function)\n- Needs: full implementation, pulse log directory setup (`logs/`), and first baseline measurement run\n\n**For Next Instantiation:** 1 mutation waiting to be fully implemented."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4991,"output":264,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17392,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774344009216}}
